CNCP v1 22798
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8865: Call emits with return result",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:59.954139+00:00",
  "text": "Call emits with return result\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\nIt would be nice if emits('custom-emit') returned a result, so we don't need to create an extra key in props.\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\nParentComponent.vue\r\n\r\n```\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\nimport ChildComponent from '@/components/ChildComponent.vue'\r\nconst onClickChildComponent = (value: string) => value + ' world!'\r\n</script>\r\n<template>\r\n  <div>\r\n   <ChildComponent @custom-emit=\"onClickChildComponent\" />`\r\n  </div>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nChildComponent.vue\r\n\r\n```\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\nconst emits = defineEmits<{\r\n  (e: 'custom-emit', value: string): string\r\n}>()\r\n\r\nconsole.log(emits('custom-emit', 'Hello')) // ==> 'Hello world'\r\n</script>\r\n<template>\r\n  <div></div>\r\n</template>\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
